                            <comment id="17910478" author="mjsax" created="Tue, 7 Jan 2025 02:24:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Just failed again on &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/kafka/pull/18402&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/kafka/pull/18402&lt;/a&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17912252" author="yu-lin chen" created="Sun, 12 Jan 2025 09:57:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Locally validated that the issue was fixed after this PR. (No error in 200 loops.) (The tests had previously failed within 20 loops.)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/kafka/commit/48b522fe86984db32556e48b799e8797ae2236ba&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/kafka/commit/48b522fe86984db32556e48b799e8797ae2236ba&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="17912511" author="yu-lin chen" created="Mon, 13 Jan 2025 13:16:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Reopen this Jira becasue other flaky issues found in CI.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;org.opentest4j.AssertionFailedError: expected: &amp;lt;2&amp;gt; but was: &amp;lt;3&amp;gt; (&lt;a href=&quot;https://ge.apache.org/s/ndoj6s2stb446/tests/task/:core:test/details/kafka.api.PlaintextAdminIntegrationTest/testConsumerGroupsDeprecatedConsumerGroupState(String%2C%20String)%5B1%5D?expanded-stacktrace=WyIxIl0&amp;amp;top-execution=2&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;Report&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;org.opentest4j.AssertionFailedError: expected: &amp;lt;true&amp;gt; but was: &amp;lt;false&amp;gt; (&lt;a href=&quot;https://ge.apache.org/s/kh3jze2tc5qeu/tests/task/:core:test/details/kafka.api.PlaintextAdminIntegrationTest/testConsumerGroupsDeprecatedConsumerGroupState(String%2C%20String)%5B1%5D?top-execution=1&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;Report&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;


&lt;p&gt;The flaky can&apos;t be reproduce in my local, but can be simulated with the attached patch &lt;span class=&quot;nobr&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/attachment/13073949/13073949_0001-Reproduce-KAFKA-18298-and-KAFKA-18297-in-ClassicConsumer.patch&quot; title=&quot;0001-Reproduce-KAFKA-18298-and-KAFKA-18297-in-ClassicConsumer.patch attached to KAFKA-18298&quot;&gt;0001-Reproduce-KAFKA-18298-and-KAFKA-18297-in-ClassicConsumer.patch&lt;sup&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;rendericon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/link_attachment_7.gif&quot; height=&quot;7&quot; width=&quot;7&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;.&#160; (Uncomment the sleep 1 sec)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The root cause is that the member rejoining group after it was removed from group. Same issue occur on &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-18297&quot; title=&quot;Fix flaky PlaintextAdminIntegrationTest.testConsumerGroups&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-18297&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-18297&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; too.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17912519" author="yu-lin chen" created="Mon, 13 Jan 2025 13:34:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Created a PR to fix the flaky in ClassicConsumer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/kafka/pull/18506&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/kafka/pull/18506&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;I would appreciate it if anyone has an idea to fix the same issue in AsyncConsumer.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17912628" author="yu-lin chen" created="Mon, 13 Jan 2025 18:01:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Create an improved PR to fully fix this flaky issue:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/kafka/pull/18513&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/kafka/pull/18513&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="17924806" author="dajac" created="Fri, 7 Feb 2025 08:16:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The PR is still ongoing. It is clear that the issue is in the test itself now so we can downgrade the priority. It is nice to have in 4.0 but not mandatory.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17926995" author="chia7712" created="Thu, 13 Feb 2025 23:35:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;this PR is merged into trunk (&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/kafka/commit/2bbd25841e5b76d99e731286899b0c5aa07fd850&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/kafka/commit/2bbd25841e5b76d99e731286899b0c5aa07fd850&lt;/a&gt;). will backport it to 4.0&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17927056" author="dajac" created="Fri, 14 Feb 2025 07:19:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Backporting to 4.0 is not worth it at our current state in the release.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
